  "riddle": "1. Seek the urban transit that spans across the bustling city of Tianjin; how many stations operate along this line, connecting its denizens to their destinations?\n\n2. From the number you just uncovered, identify the next prime sentinel that stands in waiting.\n\n3. A hub of journeys awaits at a certain railway nexus in Tianjin. In what year did this gateway to travel first welcome its passengers?\n\n4. What is the height, in meters, of the ground beneath the major railway node you just explored?\n\n5. Seek the approval rating travelers have for this transportation hub; what star rating do they bestow upon it?\n\n6. Combine the altitude you found in clue 4 with the star rating from clue 5. What total emerges from this union?\n\n7. Seek the article that discusses the tracks which allow most rapid urban transit to glide smoothly; what gauge do these trails commonly share?\n\n8. Transform 21 meters into yards for an enlightening conversion; what figure do you arrive at?\n\n9. After converting, can you find the next prime number which follows the value you have just derived?\n\n10. In the text mentioning the narrow gauge tracks, there lies a value in centimeters at the header of the article; what is this measurement?\n\n11. Just beyond this described location, there are hidden green spaces; how many parks can be found near the place known for its Niçard naming?\n\n12. Now, compute the absolute difference between the values you've gathered: take the result from clue 2, subtract that from the one found in clue 10, and apply modulo 10 to your answer. What single digit emerges from this calculation?",
